Finally, we join the "MaxTable" with the original tables based on matching the "ID" and "CreatedDate" fields to get the full records for each ID with the latest "CreatedDate". We use the Drop Table statement to remove any redundant or intermediate tables.

Note that the script assumes that the "CreatedDate" fields in both tables are stored as text values that can be concatenated, and that they have the same date format (DD/MM/YYYY,hh:mm:ss). If your date fields are stored in a different format, you'll need to adjust the script accordingly.

Also, note that the script assumes that it's acceptable to join the records on "ID" and "CreatedDate", which may not always be unique. You may need to consider additional fields or criteria to identify uniquely the records you want to join.

